The paper discusses the vulnerability of software supporting AM to cyber-attacks, intellectual property theft, and security/throughput issues of computer networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the reliability and safety of devices incorporating 3D printed parts, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of Systemic Theoretic Process Analysis (STPA) as a hazard analysis technique is also discussed, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the risks and hazards associated with AM, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
